Commentary: Bumrah steams in from over the wicket and angles it across the batter with an upright seam, on a length, outside off. Zakir Hasan lets it go as the ball does not carry through to the keeper and goes on the bounce to Rishabh Pant.
Default_Commentary: 0.1: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: Bumrah makes the batter play now and beats the bat! Angling away from the left-hander, fuller and just outside off, Zakir Hasan has a slight feel for the delivery and gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball leaves him from over-the-wicket angle.
Default_Commentary: 0.2: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: Bumrah goes searching for swing as he goes full but sprays it on the pads. Zakir Hasan misses an opportunity to tickle it fine. The ball brushes his pads and goes through to the keeper.
Default_Commentary: 0.3: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: Beaten! Closer to the off-stump line, on a good length, Zakir Hasan tries to cover the line of the ball as he looks to defend it with a straight bat. The ball goes away off the deck and beats the outside edge of Zakir.
Default_Commentary: 0.4: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: FOUR BYES! Bangladesh are underway through extras! Bumrah tries to bring the ball back into the left-hander but slips it down leg, on a fullish length. Zakir Hasan is late on the flick and the ball shoots a bit as it flies past the outstretched right palm of the leaping Rishabh Pant for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 0.5: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, 4 Byes.

Commentary: Bumrah gets the line right this time, shaping in, full and attacking the stumps, Zakir Hasan hurriedly gets his bat out in front of the front pad and nudges it to mid-wicket.
Default_Commentary: 0.6: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: Siraj charges in from over the wicket and bashes the hard length, not much movement off the deck, on off. Shadman Islam hops and rides the bounce to stab it down with a straight bat.
Default_Commentary: 1.1: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Siraj hurls it full and gets a good inward shape into the left-hander, on middle and leg, Shadman Islam accounts for the inward movement and clips it behind square on the leg side. Jasprit Bumrah at deep fine leg mops it up to his right. Shadman gets off the mark with a couple of runs.
Default_Commentary: 1.2: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, 2 runs.

Commentary: Siraj drags the length back and bowls it around middle and leg, Shadman Islam gets on top of the bounce and tucks it through square leg along the ground. Ravichandran Ashwin gives it a chase and due to the outfield being a bit soft, he opts not to put in the slide. Two runs taken.
Default_Commentary: 1.3: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, 2 runs.

Commentary: Beauty! Siraj lands it on a back of a length, just outside the off-stump line, Shadman Islam stays on the back foot to keep it out with a straight bat. The ball nips away off the deck and whizzes past the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 1.4: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Siraj continues to hit the deck hard, on middle and leg, on a back of a length, Shadman Islam rises with the bounce and works it in front of square leg.
Default_Commentary: 1.5: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Fuller in length now by Siraj and at the stumps, Shadman Islam presents a straight bat and knocks it back to the bowler. Siraj picks the ball up in his follow through and fakes a throw towards the batting end, which brings out a loud cheer from the crowd.
Default_Commentary: 1.6: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Bumrah sprays it down leg in search of the inswinger, on a length, Zakir Hasan fails to get any bat on it as he tries to help it away.
Default_Commentary: 2.1: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: Bumrah changes his angle of attack as he comes from around the wicket and angles it in, on a length, on off and middle, Zakir Hasan closes the bat face a bit early as he looks to work it on the leg side. Gets a soft leading edge that rolls beside the pitch on the off side.
Default_Commentary: 2.2: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: Keeps it full does Bumrah, on off, Zakir Hasan lunges and presents a straight bat to defend it on the leg side.
Default_Commentary: 2.3: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: Full at 134.6 kph, on off and middle, Zakir Hasan gets his weight on the front foot and firms the drive but can't get it past the man at mid on.
Default_Commentary: 2.4: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: Shaping away in the air, on a length and in the corridor of off, Zakir Hasan shoulders arms watchully.
Default_Commentary: 2.5: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: Sharp stop! Bumrah makes the ball come back into the left-hander, full and on off, Zakir Hasan frees his arms and cracks the drive but Ravindra Jadeja at backward point dives quickly to his left and makes the stop.
Default_Commentary: 2.6: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: Angling across the batter from the over-the-wicket angle, on a good length, outside off, Shadman Islam stays back in his crease and covers the off pole before making the leave.
Default_Commentary: 3.1: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Edged away! A fortuitous boundary for Shadman Islam! Siraj bowls it with a scrambled seam, on a back of a length, around off, Shadman Islam hops on the back foot and pushes at the delivery tentatively. Gets an outside edge that flies past the leaping Yashasvi Jaiswal to his left at gully for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 3.2: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, Four!

Commentary: This is on a back of a length, on off, Shadman Islam gets behind the line of the ball nicely this time and blocks it down the deck.
Default_Commentary: 3.3: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Edged but it falls short! A touch fuller and going across the batter, on off, Shadman Islam defends away from his body as he gets on the front foot but does so with soft hands. It saves him as the edge falls short of the diving Yashasvi Jaiswal at gully.
Default_Commentary: 3.4: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Half a shout for LBW but that looked high! On a back of a length, on off and middle, Shadman Islam goes deep in his crease and tries to work it away off his pads on the leg side. Gets beaten on the inside edge and wears it high on the thigh pad.
Default_Commentary: 3.5: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Fuller in length, on off, Shadman Islam solidly blocks it in front of mid off.
Default_Commentary: 3.6: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Angling in and then nipping away off the deck, on a length, outside off, Zakir Hasan reads it well and lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Default_Commentary: 4.1: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: Fuller and around the sixth stump line, Zakir Hasan presses forward and eases the drive with a straight bat to mid off.
Default_Commentary: 4.2: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: Another that angles in and straightens off the deck, on a good length, Zakir Hasan does well not to go chasing at the delivery and tucks his bat inside the line of the ball to let it be.
Default_Commentary: 4.3: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: Slanting in, on a good length, on middle and leg, Zakir Hasan is beaten for pace and a bit of extra bounce results in the ball zipping past the defence of Zakir and he wears it high on the back leg.
Default_Commentary: 4.4: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: At the batter, on a hard length, Zakir Hasan lets the ball come to him and covers the line of the ball to defend it on the leg side.
Default_Commentary: 4.5: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: This is on a back of a length, over off, Zakir Hasan gets on his toes and punches it with a straight bat back to the bowler. Bumrah yet to concede a run off the bat.
Default_Commentary: 4.6: Jasprit Bumrah to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: Angling across the batter, on a length, Shadman Islam shoulders arms.
Default_Commentary: 5.1: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Slanting away, on a good length, on off, Shadman Islam hangs back and looks to punch it away. Toe-ends his shot in front of cover.
Default_Commentary: 5.2: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: This one comes back into the left-hander but the line is down leg, on a short of a length, Shadman Islam gets inside the line to help it away but misses.
Default_Commentary: 5.3: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: At 137.9 kph, on a hard length, around off, Shadman Islam waits on the back foot and plays it right under his eyes. Taps it beside the pitch on the leg side and calls Zakir through for a quick single.
Default_Commentary: 5.4: Mohammed Siraj to Shadman Islam, 1 run.

Commentary: A touch fuller from Siraj, shaping in, on off, Zakir Hasan gets behind the line of the ball and pats it with a straight bat to the right of the bowler.
Default_Commentary: 5.5: Mohammed Siraj to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: Full again and swinging in, on middle, Zakir Hasan uses his feet to negate the movement. Closes the bat face just a bit and works it in front of mid-wicket.
Default_Commentary: 5.6: Mohammed Siraj to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Easy pickings! On a length and on the pads from around the wicket, Shadman Islam gets inside the line quickly and plays it late. Hops and glances it to the right of deep fine leg for a boundary. First runs off the bat of Bumrah's bowling.
Default_Commentary: 6.1: Jasprit Bumrah to Shadman Islam, Four!

Commentary: In the corridor of off, on a good length, outside off, Shadman Islam shoulders arms.
Default_Commentary: 6.2: Jasprit Bumrah to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Fired in at 143.7 kph, full and attacking the stumps, Shadman Islam gets on the front foot and wrists it towards mid-wicket.
Default_Commentary: 6.3: Jasprit Bumrah to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Bumrah pulls his length back and gets the ball to angle back in, around the sixth stump line. Shadman Islam knows where his off pole is and covers it before making the leave.
Default_Commentary: 6.4: Jasprit Bumrah to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: This leaves the batter, fuller and at 136.2 kph, outside off with an upright seam. Shadman Islam is a bit tentative as he presents an angled bat to keep it out. The ball nips away and zips past the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 6.5: Jasprit Bumrah to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Not quite from the middle of the bat but Shadman will take it! Full and shaping away, on off, Shadman Islam looks to drive it down the ground but the late away movement catches the outside edge. It races past Ravindra Jadeja at backward point for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 6.6: Jasprit Bumrah to Shadman Islam, Four!

Commentary: Ashwin starts from around the wicket and darts it in, on a nagging length, at the pads, Zakir Hasan hangs back and tries to whip it away. The ball lobs off his pads and drops in front of square leg for a leg bye.
Default_Commentary: 7.1: Ravichandran Ashwin to Zakir Hasan, Leg bye.

Commentary: FOUR! Fine shot! Full and sliding down leg, Shadman Islam gets inside the line of the ball and rolls his wrists on the ball to sweep it fine. Gets it through short fine leg for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 7.2: Ravichandran Ashwin to Shadman Islam, Four!

Commentary: Full and at the stumps, Shadman Islam gets on the front foot and blocks it out.
Default_Commentary: 7.3: Ravichandran Ashwin to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Ashwin drags his length back and slants it in, on middle and leg, Shadman Islam lunges and defends it in front of short leg.
Default_Commentary: 7.4: Ravichandran Ashwin to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: A bit of air given on this occasion by Ashwin, very full, at the toes, Shadman Islam squeezes it out in front of short mid-wicket.
Default_Commentary: 7.5: Ravichandran Ashwin to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Beaten! The first sign of turn and bounce on this surface. Ashwin slows it up a touch and keeps the length away from the batter, Shadman Islam does not get a big stride and fails to get to the pitch of the ball to smother the spin. The ball pitches and then spins away to go past the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 7.6: Ravichandran Ashwin to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: At 133.7 kph, on a good length, shaping away, outside off, Zakir Hasan pushes at the delivery away from his body. Luckily for him, he does not nick it behind. The ball swings goes further away after going past the batter and Rishabh Pant takes it low to his left.
Default_Commentary: 8.1: Akash Deep to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: In the channel on off, on a good length, Zakir Hasan punches it from the crease but straight to cover.
Default_Commentary: 8.2: Akash Deep to Zakir Hasan, No run.

Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Sharp catch by Yashasvi Jaiswal! Immediate impact for Akash Deep. Akash lands it on a good length, in the channel on off from around the wicket. Zakir Hasan plays the line of the ball as he looks to defend it with a straight bat. The ball straightens off the deck and catches the outside edge. Jaiswal at gully is in really tight and he reacts quickly. Goes low to his right and grabs it. Jaiswal claims it but the umpires ask Zakir to wait as they refer it upstairs. The third umpire looks at multiple angles but the replays appear a bit blurry. He does not have conclusive evidence to suggest that the ball has been grassed. He concludes that Jaiswal has his fingers underneath the ball and OUT flashes on the big screen. Zakir goes for a 24-ball duck.
Default_Commentary: 8.3: Akash Deep to Zakir Hasan, OUT! c Yashasvi Jaiswal b Akash Deep.
Howout: c Yashasvi Jaiswal b Akash Deep

Commentary: Angling in and then going away, on a length, on off, Mominul Haque has a slight feel for the delivery and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 8.4: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Not close enough to make the batter play, on a good length, outside off, Mominul Haque lets it go.
Default_Commentary: 8.5: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Beaten! Full and around off, Mominul Haque is rooted to the crease as he goes for a straight drive. Gets beaten as the ball nips away to go past the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 8.6: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Turning in, on middle and leg, Shadman Islam tucks it fine to deep fine leg for a brace.
Default_Commentary: 9.1: Ravichandran Ashwin to Shadman Islam, 2 runs.

Commentary: Flighted up, on middle and off, Shadman Islam gets a good stride out and pushes it to mid off.
Default_Commentary: 9.2: Ravichandran Ashwin to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Fuller and on middle and leg, Shadman Islam keeps it out on the leg side.
Default_Commentary: 9.3: Ravichandran Ashwin to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Fires it quicker and fuller, on middle, Shadman Islam eases it back to the bowler.
Default_Commentary: 9.4: Ravichandran Ashwin to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: That's a beauty from Ashwin! Gets the ball to grip the surface a bit, on a nagging length just outside off, Shadman Islam looks to tuck it across the line but misses.
Default_Commentary: 9.5: Ravichandran Ashwin to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Full, on middle and off, Shadman Islam gets a big stride out in an attempt to block but gets an outside edge to backward point.
Default_Commentary: 9.6: Ravichandran Ashwin to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Going away off the deck, on a back of a length, on off, Mominul Haque dabs it off the back foot to backward point.
Default_Commentary: 10.1: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Fuller in length now, on off, Mominul Haque lets the ball come to him and defends it on the off side.
Default_Commentary: 10.2: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Goes wide of the crease on the around-the-wicket angle and lands it on a back of a length, on off, Mominul Haque steers it from the crease to backward point.
Default_Commentary: 10.3: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Closer to the off-stump line, fuller too, Mominul Haque covers his off stump and makes the leave.
Default_Commentary: 10.4: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Serves it on a length, on the sixth stump line, Mominul Haque shoulders arms watchfully.
Default_Commentary: 10.5: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Angling in, on a good length, on off, Mominul Haque defends it right under his eyes. Another maiden for Akash Deep.
Default_Commentary: 10.6: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Drifting in, full and on off, Shadman Islam lunges and checks the drive to mid off.
Default_Commentary: 11.1: Ravichandran Ashwin to Shadman Islam, No run.

Commentary: Slower through the air and on a nagging length, on off, Shadman Islam comes forward to defend but the ball spins away to catch the outside edge. The ball rolls to the right of short third for a single.
Default_Commentary: 11.2: Ravichandran Ashwin to Shadman Islam, 1 run.

Commentary: With a first slip and gully in place, Ashwin bowls it a bit short, on off, Mominul Haque stays back and stabs it down the deck.
Default_Commentary: 11.3: Ravichandran Ashwin to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Ashwin loops it up and gets the ball to spin away from the left-hander, fuller in length, Mominul Haque reaches out in front for the sweep but fails to connect.
Default_Commentary: 11.4: Ravichandran Ashwin to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: This is fuller and quicker, on off, Mominul Haque presses forward to keep it out.
Default_Commentary: 11.5: Ravichandran Ashwin to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Fired down leg by Ashwin, Mominul Haque gets inside the line to sweep it fine but misses.
Default_Commentary: 11.6: Ravichandran Ashwin to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: OUT LBW! A big, big shout for LBW but the umpire remains unmoved! Akash Deep is pretty convinced and after having a chat with Rishabh Pant, Rohit Sharma takes the review. It looked to be going down leg from the around-the-wicket angle. With an upright seam, Akash bowls it on a good length, on middle and leg, Shadman Islam hops and shapes up to work it across the line. Gets beaten on the inside edge and wears it near the knee roll on the front pad. There is no bat involved on UltraEdge and the Ball Tracking shows three reds with the ball hitting the leg stump, much to the surprise of Rohit Sharma and Co. The on-field decision will have to be overturned and Bangladesh have now lost both their openers. Shadman Islam walks back for 24 (36) and Bangladesh are now 29/2!
Default_Commentary: 12.1: Akash Deep to Shadman Islam, OUT! lbw b Akash Deep.

Commentary: At 136.9 kph, sprayed down leg, on a length, Najmul Hossain Shanto misses the tickle as the ball brushes his pads and goes on the bounce to the right of the keeper, Rishabh Pant who makes a good diving stop.
Default_Commentary: 12.2: Akash Deep to Najmul Hossain Shanto, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Streaky but they all count! Deep serves it fuller in length, in the channel on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it away from his body but does so with soft hands. Gets an outside edge that races through the gap between gully and backward point for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 12.3: Akash Deep to Najmul Hossain Shanto, Four!

Commentary: In the corridor of off, on a good length, left alone by Shanto.
Default_Commentary: 12.4: Akash Deep to Najmul Hossain Shanto, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Nothing streaky about this one. A lovely shot from the Bangladesh skipper. Fuller in length from Deep, around off, Najmul Hossain Shanto gets his weight on the front foot and leans into the drive. Times the drive to the left of mid off for his second boundary.
Default_Commentary: 12.5: Akash Deep to Najmul Hossain Shanto, Four!

Commentary: Deep changes his angle of attack as he comes from over the wicket now and angles it across the batter, on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto has a slight poke at the away-going delivery and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 12.6: Akash Deep to Najmul Hossain Shanto, No run.

Commentary: Siraj comes back into the attack and steams in from over the wicket, lands it on a fuller length, well outside off, Mominul Haque leaves it alone.
Default_Commentary: 13.1: Mohammed Siraj to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Bowls it full and on off, Mominul Haque leans ahead and taps it to covers for a quick single.
Default_Commentary: 13.2: Mohammed Siraj to Mominul Haque, 1 run.

Commentary: FOUR! Edged and it races past Yashasvi Jaiswal! Siraj keeps the length fuller and angles it across, just around off, Najmul Hossain Shanto with soft hands looks to play at it with a straight bat but gets a thick outside edge past diving Jaiswal at gully to his right for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 13.3: Mohammed Siraj to Najmul Hossain Shanto, Four!

Commentary: A huge shout for LBW, but the umpire turns it down! After a long chat with the bowler and Rishabh Pant, skipper Rohit Sharma sends it upstairs. This is on a back of a length, around middle and leg, nipping back in sharply. Najmul Hossain Shanto hops back and looks to tuck it away on the leg side but misses and gets pinged high on the thigh pad. The UltraEdge shows no spike but the Ball Tracking confirms the ball to be pitching down leg. The on-field call stays and India burn a review.
Default_Commentary: 13.4: Mohammed Siraj to Najmul Hossain Shanto, No run.

Commentary: On a length, angling across, well outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto leaves it alone.
Default_Commentary: 13.5: Mohammed Siraj to Najmul Hossain Shanto, No run.

Commentary: A tad bit wide, full and angling away from the batter, Najmul Hossain Shanto gets a good stride in and then makes the leave.
Default_Commentary: 13.6: Mohammed Siraj to Najmul Hossain Shanto, No run.

Commentary: Comes from around the wicket and lands it on a hard length, outside off, coming in with the angle, Mominul Haque sees the line and opts to let it be.
Default_Commentary: 14.1: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Bangs this into the deck on a good length and gets the ball to shoot and shape away a bit off the deck, Mominul Haque is drawn into the shot and looks to poke at it away from his body. Gets beaten on the outside edge with the extra bounce and shape.
Default_Commentary: 14.2: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: On a back of a length, over off, Mominul Haque confidently pats it down to point.
Default_Commentary: 14.3: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Beaten again! Akash Deep is hitting those probing lines and making a real impact! Hits the hard length, in and around off and gets the ball to straighten off the deck a bit. Mominul Haque looks for a gentle push on the front foot but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 14.4: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Beaten off the backfoot this time! Drags the length a tad short, on off, with an upright seam and gets the ball to shape away just enough to beat the outside edge of Mominul Haque's bat as he looks to keep it out off the back foot.
Default_Commentary: 14.5: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Good length, on middle and off, Mominul Haque taps it to backward point. End of another solid over from Akash Deep!
Default_Commentary: 14.6: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Edged and goes through, yet again! Siraj bowls this fuller in length, on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto gets a good stride out and just opens the bat face enough for the ball to get a healthy outside edge through the gap between the slip cordon and gully for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 15.1: Mohammed Siraj to Najmul Hossain Shanto, Four!

Commentary: Angling across on a fuller length, on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto leans on and blocks it to the off side.
Default_Commentary: 15.2: Mohammed Siraj to Najmul Hossain Shanto, No run.

Commentary: Hits the hard length and angles it across, outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto attempts to play at it with soft hands and away from his body. Gets beaten on the outside edge, quite comprehensively!
Default_Commentary: 15.3: Mohammed Siraj to Najmul Hossain Shanto, No run.

Commentary: Attacks the stumps, on a fuller length, Najmul Hossain Shanto covers the line well and taps it to mid on.
Default_Commentary: 15.4: Mohammed Siraj to Najmul Hossain Shanto, No run.

Commentary: Too wide outside off, fuller in length, Najmul Hossain Shanto sees the line and leaves it alone.
Default_Commentary: 15.5: Mohammed Siraj to Najmul Hossain Shanto, No run.

Commentary: Gets the line closer to the off-stump, on a hard length, Najmul Hossain Shanto dabs it out in front of backward point.
Default_Commentary: 15.6: Mohammed Siraj to Najmul Hossain Shanto, No run.

Commentary: Angling in, on a good length, on off, Mominul Haque tries to dive it straight but mistimes it back to the bowler who makes half a stop on his follow through.
Default_Commentary: 16.1: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: Outside off, on a length, Mominul Haque charges towards the line of the ball, only to hold his wrists high and make the leave.
Default_Commentary: 16.2: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Up and over! Mominul Haque gets a freebie and makes the most of it. Akash Deep digs one short and outside off, asking to be hit, Haque cuts it aerially over backward point and gets his first boundary.
Default_Commentary: 16.3: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, Four!

Commentary: Into the pads, on a length, Mominul Haque clips it to deep fine leg for a single.
Default_Commentary: 16.4: Akash Deep to Mominul Haque, 1 run.

Commentary: From the over-the-wicket angle, Deep bowls it full and outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto shoulders arms.
Default_Commentary: 16.5: Akash Deep to Najmul Hossain Shanto, No run.

Commentary: Good length, over middle and off, Najmul Hossain Shanto hops and covers the line before stabbing it down the deck.
Default_Commentary: 16.6: Akash Deep to Najmul Hossain Shanto, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Mominul Haque plays this very well and gets another boundary off his name. Siraj bangs it into the deck, angling it away, just outside off, Mominul Haque quickly shifts his weight back and delicately ramps it over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 17.1: Mohammed Siraj to Mominul Haque, Four!

Commentary: At 134.1 kph, on a length, outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim gets on the front foot nicely and opens the bat face slightly to guide it towards gully. Yashasvi Jaiswal dives to his right and parries the ball to his right, in front of backward point.

Commentary: In the channel on off, on a good length, Mushfiqur Rahim initially thinks about playing this one but in the end, makes the wise decision of letting it be.

Commentary: OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! Jasprit Bumrah with the first strike for India on Day 4! Steams in from over the wicket and goes slightly wide of the crease, on a good length. The ball pitches well outside off and Mushfiqur Rahim shuffles to cover the off pole. Rahim thinks he has his off stump covered as he hoists his bat up but the ball jags back in a long way to clatter into the top of the off stump. Mushfiqur Rahim walks back for 11(32) and Bangladesh are now 112/4!
Default_Commentary: 40.2: Jasprit Bumrah to Mushfiqur Rahim, OUT! b Jasprit Bumrah.

Commentary: Given caught but successfully overturned by Mominul Haque! Siraj tucks the batter up for room as he comes from over the wicket and bangs it on a back of a length, around the pads, Mominul Haque hops to tuck it away but misses. Gets beaten on the inside edge and it lobs to Yashasvi Jaiswal at a deepish short leg who takes it low, moving away to his right. The finger goes up but Mominul Haque reviews it straight away. Has this come off his thigh pad? The first replay does seem to suggest so and it is confirmed by the UltraEdge. The third umpire wants to confirm whether it has come off the gloves after it lobbed off the thigh pad. It has made no contact with the glove and the on-field decision will have to be overturned.
Default_Commentary: 45.1: Mohammed Siraj to Mominul Haque, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! And that will be FIFTY for Mominul Haque! Siraj bends his back and digs it in short but does not get it high enough to trouble the batter. Mominul Haque rolls his wrists on the ball and pulls it all along the ground through square leg. 20th fifty for the southpaw in Tests. This has been a measured inning from Mominul and he will look to convert this one into a three-figure score.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! That's a fine catch! Rohit Sharma has plucked that out of thin air. Excellent stuff. Das steps out and also makes room. This is fuller. He hits it quite nicely. Looks to go over mid off. Seems to have cleared him too but Rohit stretches his right hand upwards and this one stays in. Rohit is ecstatic and so are the Indians. That's an important wicket. Das goes for 13 (30). Bangladesh are now 148/5.

Howout: c Rohit Sharma b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! That's a seriously good catch! Second excellent catch from India today. This is probably better than the first one. Ashwin comes on and strikes. Excellent bowling change. However, that shot was a poor one from Shakib. Not sure if he needed to play another one after getting a boundary the ball before. He steps out. Ashwin slows it up and drags his length back a touch. Shakib looks to go over mid off but is through the shot early. It goes off the toe end towards mid off. Siraj backtracks, he seems to have misjudged it but then leaps and takes it behind his head and tumbles over as the ball sticks in his left hand. Shakib falls for 9 (17). Bangladesh are now 170/6.
Default_Commentary: 55.6: Ravichandran Ashwin to Shakib Al Hasan, OUT! c Mohammed Siraj b Ravichandran Ashwin.
Howout: c Mohammed Siraj b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: FOUR! HUNDRED for Mominul Haque! What a brilliant way to reach the milestone! A thoroughly deserved century, showcasing his resilience and class. Despite a shaky start on Day 1, Mominul has steadily grown in confidence, and this knock is a testament to how well he has constructed this inning. Tossed up from Ashwin, on middle, Mominul Haque yet again, brings the sweep shot out and executes it to perfection hitting the ball behind square of the wicket on the leg side for a boundary. Mominul acknowledges the crowd and his teammates with a humble raise of the bat, soaking it all in!

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! Jasprit Bumrah has his man and India get the much-needed breakthrough! He steams in from over the wicket and hits the deck hard, on a length, over off with the angle coming into the right-hander. The ball nips away just enough and catches a healthy outside edge as Mehidy Hasan rocks back and has a slight poke at the delivery. The ball goes straight to Shubman Gill at first slip who gobbles it up around his stomach with both hands. A bit of a send-off by Bumrah as he claps and celebrates while looking towards Mehidy. Mehidy goes for 20 (42) and Bangladesh are now 224/7.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! 300 TEST WICKETS FOR JADEJA! The softest of dismissals and Bangladesh are bowled out for 233. Indians erupt in celebration, gathering around Jadeja to applaud his remarkable milestone. This is tossed up full, on middle and off by Jadeja and he gets the ball to grip and turn away, Khaled Ahmed tries to play it across the line and closes the bat face a bit too early. A leading edge is found and the ball balloons behind to the left of the bowler. Jadeja moves across quickly and grabs a simple catch over his left shoulder. Jadeja becomes the third Indian after Kapil Dev and Ravichandran Ashwin to achieve the double of scoring 3000 runs and taking 300 wickets in Test cricket.
Default_Commentary: 74.2: Ravindra Jadeja to Khaled Ahmed, OUT! c & b Ravindra Jadeja.

Commentary: RUN OUT CHANCE MISSED! A big, big mix-up and Khaled Ahmed has made a mess of it. Khaled bowls it full and outside off, Virat Kohli reaches and goes for an expansive drive. Gets an inside edge onto the pads and the ball goes nowhere. It rolls near his feet but Kohli thinks that it has gone away for him to take the single. He sets off for the single but gets sent back by Pant halfway through the run. Virat is nowhere in the frame when Khaled Ahmed charges in off his follow through and bends to pick the ball up. He is inches away from the stumps at the batting end and has all the time in the world to walk towards the stumps and take the bails off.
